00:32:26.304 --> 00:32:33.644
- No, it's easier than that. You just reason
about it. First of all, you just reason.

00:32:34.864 --> 00:32:38.784
no matter, no matter what
happens, at some point in order

00:32:38.884 --> 00:32:42.814
for that large language model to
be a digital worker... Let's just,

00:32:42.984 --> 00:32:46.894
let's just use that metaphor. Let's
say that we want the LLM to be a

00:32:46.944 --> 00:32:48.384
digital worker. What does that have to do?

00:32:49.224 --> 00:32:53.204
It has to access ground truth.
That's our file system. It has

00:32:53.244 --> 00:32:57.224
to be able to do research. It doesn't know
everything. We don't have... And I don't wanna

00:32:57.264 --> 00:33:01.064
wait until this AI becomes,
you know, universally

00:33:01.304 --> 00:33:05.154
smart about everything, past,
present, and future before I

00:33:05.184 --> 00:33:08.884
make it useful. And so therefore, I
might as well let it go do research.

00:33:09.544 --> 00:33:12.324
It's obviously, if it wants to
help me, it's gotta use my tools.

00:33:13.324 --> 00:33:17.284
You know, a lot of people would say,
"You know AI is gonna completely

00:33:17.304 --> 00:33:20.494
destroy software. We don't need software anymore.
We don't even need tools anymore." That's

00:33:20.504 --> 00:33:24.534
ridiculous. Let's use the...
Let's use a thought experiment.

00:33:25.514 --> 00:33:29.414
And you could just sit there,
