00:33:29.464 --> 00:33:33.334
and think about all these things, and it
would become completely obvious. Like, if I

00:33:33.364 --> 00:33:37.224
were to create the most amazing- the

00:33:37.404 --> 00:33:41.044
most amazing agent that we can
imagine in the next 10 years.

00:33:41.464 --> 00:33:45.364
Let's say it'd be a humanoid robot. If
that humanoid robot were to be created,

00:33:46.444 --> 00:33:49.064
is it more likely that the
humanoid robot comes into my house

00:33:50.204 --> 00:33:53.964
and uses the tools that I have to
do the work that it needs to do?

00:33:54.644 --> 00:33:58.604
Or does this hand turns
into a 10-pound hammer in

00:33:58.724 --> 00:34:02.464
one instance, turns into a
scalpel in another instance,

00:34:02.984 --> 00:34:06.904
and in order to boil water, it
beams, you know, microwaves out

00:34:06.944 --> 00:34:10.464
of its fingers? You know, or is it more
likely just to use a microwave, you

00:34:10.504 --> 00:34:12.854
know? And the first time it
goes up to the microwave,

00:34:13.684 --> 00:34:17.344
it probably doesn't know how to use it.
But that's okay. It's connected to the

00:34:17.384 --> 00:34:20.724
